===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fr|en}} {{term|limonade|lang=fr}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˌlɛmənˈeɪd/|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|eɪd|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# A [[still]] [[beverage]] consisting of lemon and [[sugar]], sometimes ice, and water, used mainly as a [[refreshment]].
# A [[carbonated]] [[beverage]] made from lemon or artificial lemon flavouring/flavoring, water and sugar.

====Usage notes====
In locations where the meaning as a carbonated beverage is common, the still beverage is often called "homemade lemonade".

